{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BCoCX2rJHEinNFjHespCZR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<server description=\"Roster Jakarta EE Application\">\n     3→    <featureManager>\n     4→        <feature>jakartaee-10.0</feature>\n     5→    </featureManager>\n     6→\n     7→    <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\"\n     8→                  httpPort=\"8080\"\n     9→                  httpsPort=\"9443\"\n    10→                  host=\"*\" />\n    11→\n    12→    <!-- H2 Database Library -->\n    13→    <library id=\"h2Lib\">\n    14→        <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib\" includes=\"h2-*.jar\"/>\n    15→    </library>\n    16→\n    17→    <!-- DataSource for H2 in-memory database -->\n    18→    <dataSource id=\"rosterDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/rosterDS\" type=\"javax.sql.DataSource\">\n    19→        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    20→        <properties.generic URL=\"jdbc:h2:mem:roster;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\"\n    21→                            user=\"sa\"\n    22→                            password=\"\"/>\n    23→    </dataSource>\n    24→\n    25→    <!-- Application deployment -->\n    26→    <webApplication id=\"roster\" location=\"roster.war\" contextRoot=\"/\">\n    27→        <classloader commonLibraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    28→    </webApplication>\n    29→</server>\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98f0c157-25c8-4522-ad5d-c073f4a9b639","uuid":"be0ef48a-53f2-4e22-9629-d2f21a277548"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012VB2RCws93hXpiXyeuDmRN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The error says \"Searched in: []\" which means it couldn't find the directory. The problem is likely the `liberty:deploy` created a different config. But looking at the output, the server starts and the app starts. But the H2 error happens before the app starts. However, the app did start (\"Application roster started in 1.790 seconds\").\n\nWait, the error says the H2 driver can't be found, but the server still started. The problem might be that the `dataSource` config fails to load the H2 driver. Let me check if the liberty image has a different default server config dir. The previous output showed the jar IS at `/opt/ol/wlp/usr/servers/defaultServer/lib/h2-2.2.224.jar`, so `${server.config.dir}` should resolve to `/opt/ol/wlp/usr/servers/defaultServer`.\n\nLet me check the actual deployed server.xml:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":900,"cache_read_input_tokens":103593,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":900,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":340},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98f0c157-25c8-4522-ad5d-c073f4a9b639","uuid":"c385177b-1ba0-4783-a7f7-9c9fdbb1b468"}
