{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01J99VaMaLjEvVTUQmJyBcHe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait, the `properties` element in Liberty doesn't have `url`. For H2, you need `properties.generic` with a specific approach. Actually, looking at the error more carefully - the `URL` attribute in `properties.generic` should work. But the EclipseLink provider might look for the `url` through a JPA property. Let me check if the persistence.xml needs to specify the URL instead.\n\nActually, looking at the Liberty docs, for `properties.generic`, `URL` is the correct attribute name (capital U). But OpenLiberty's EclipseLink persistence might need the datasource properties to be specified with `jakarta.persistence.jdbc.url` in persistence.xml.\n\nLet me take a different approach - configure the datasource URL via `properties.h2.database` which is the Liberty-specific H2 properties config:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1104,"cache_read_input_tokens":115610,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1104,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":784},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98f0c157-25c8-4522-ad5d-c073f4a9b639","uuid":"8fa04706-b567-462f-9292-098e91b45136"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01J99VaMaLjEvVTUQmJyBcHe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Em3aEsVdL6No7BPD8T3iJ7","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__persistence__roster__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output/src/main/liberty/config/server.xml","old_string":"    <!-- DataSource for H2 in-memory database -->\n    <dataSource id=\"rosterDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/rosterDS\">\n        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n        <properties url=\"jdbc:h2:mem:roster;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\"\n                    user=\"sa\"\n                    password=\"\"/>\n    </dataSource>\n\n    <!-- Default DataSource (same as rosterDS, for JPA default persistence unit) -->\n    <dataSource id=\"DefaultDataSource\" jndiName=\"jdbc/DefaultDataSource\">\n        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n        <properties url=\"jdbc:h2:mem:roster;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\"\n                    user=\"sa\"\n                    password=\"\"/>\n    </dataSource>","new_string":"    <!-- DataSource for H2 in-memory database -->\n    <dataSource id=\"rosterDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/rosterDS\">\n        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n        <properties.generic databaseName=\"mem:roster\" URL=\"jdbc:h2:mem:roster;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\"\n                    user=\"sa\"\n                    password=\"\"/>\n    </dataSource>\n\n    <!-- Default DataSource (same as rosterDS, for JPA default persistence unit) -->\n    <dataSource id=\"DefaultDataSource\" jndiName=\"jdbc/DefaultDataSource\">\n        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n        <properties.generic databaseName=\"mem:roster\" URL=\"jdbc:h2:mem:roster;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\"\n                    user=\"sa\"\n                    password=\"\"/>\n    </dataSource>"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage"