{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LWdNhLXkZQeS9q9TBYPjvo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_015pnHSSEZETd9j7nP3vMhjF","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__persistence__roster__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output/src/main/liberty/config/server.xml","content":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<server description=\"Roster Jakarta EE Application\">\n\n    <featureManager>\n        <feature>webProfile-10.0</feature>\n    </featureManager>\n\n    <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\"\n                  httpPort=\"8080\"\n                  httpsPort=\"9443\"\n                  host=\"*\" />\n\n    <!-- H2 Database Library -->\n    <library id=\"h2Lib\">\n        <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib\" includes=\"h2-*.jar\"/>\n    </library>\n\n    <!-- DataSource for H2 in-memory database using JDBC driver class -->\n    <dataSource id=\"rosterDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/rosterDS\">\n        <jdbcDriver javax.sql.DataSource=\"org.h2.jdbcx.JdbcDataSource\" libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n        <properties URL=\"jdbc:h2:mem:roster;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\"\n                    user=\"sa\"\n                    password=\"\"/>\n    </dataSource>\n\n    <!-- Application deployment -->\n    <webApplication id=\"roster\" location=\"roster.war\" contextRoot=\"/\">\n        <classloader commonLibraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    </webApplication>\n</server>\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":974,"cache_read_input_tokens":117646,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":974,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":514},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98f0c157-25c8-4522-ad5d-c073f4a9b639","uuid":"6a0b2470-cea0-4c04-9f7b-0d50d19dc32c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015pnHSSEZETd9j7nP3vMhjF","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__persistence__roster__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output/src/main/liberty/config/server.xml has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<server description=\"Roster Jakarta EE Application\">\n     3→\n     4→    <featureManager>\n     5→        <feature>webProfile-10.0</feature>\n     6→    </featureManager>\n     7→\n     8→    <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\"\n     9→                  httpPort=\"8080\"\n    10→                  httpsPort=\"9443\"\n    11→                  host=\"*\" />\n    12→\n    13→    <!-- H2 Database Library -->\n    14→    <library id=\"h2Lib\">\n    15→        <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib\" includes=\"h2-*.jar\"/>\n    16→    </library>\n    17→\n    18→    <!-- DataSource for H2 in-memory database using JDBC driver class -->\n    19→    <dataSource id=\"rosterDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/rosterDS\">\n    20→        <jdbcDriver javax.sql.DataSource=\"org.h2.jdbcx.JdbcDataSource\" libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    21→        <properties URL=\"jdbc:h2:mem:roster;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\"\n    22→                    user=\"sa\"\n    23→                    password=\"\"/>\n    24→    </dataSource>\n    25→\n    26→    <!-- Application deployment -->\n    27→    <webApplication id=\"roster\" location=\"roster.war\" contextRoot=\"/\">\n    28→        <classloader commonLibraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    29→    </webApplication>\n    30→</server>\n    31→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98f0c157-25c8-4522-ad5d-c073f4a9b639","uuid":"26937741-a5b3-4f14-a596-23fca13ff7b0"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01QsBLTrXLZzpqVZambQD6Uf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Actually, I think the real issue with `properties.generic` was that `URL` (capital) is correct BUT there might be a mapping issue. Let me search for the exact correct way to configure H2 with Open Liberty and EclipseLink:\n\nThe H2 driver's `JdbcDataSource` class has a `setUrl()` method, so the property name should be `url` (lowercase) when using `<properties>` element. The `<properties.generic>` element maps `URL` to `java.sql.DriverManager.getConnection(URL, ...)`. But EclipseLink uses the JTA datasource to get connections - it shouldn't need the URL.\n\nLet me rethink this. The error was: `\"URL format error; must be 'jdbc:h2:...' but is ''\"` - the URL was empty. This means the datasource connection is failing because it can't find the URL.\n\nFor `<properties>` element in Liberty, the attribute names map to setter methods on the datasource class. So `<properties URL=\"...\"/>` would call `setURL()` on `JdbcDataSource`. H2's `JdbcDataSource` has `setUrl(String)` not `setURL(String)`. So the correct attribute is `url` lowercase:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1107,"cache_read_input_tokens":118620,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1107,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":533},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98f0c157-25c8-4522-ad5d-c073f4a9b639","uuid":"6fc9c613-6705-475d-9d9b-ae016d94685d"}
