{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01KnYdHdBtxiakYmrYebWg7n","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Those are just the expected drop-and-create warnings. The actual API error isn't logged with a stack trace. The issue might be that `@Transactional` isn't getting intercepted in Jakarta EE. In standard Jakarta EE, `@Transactional` requires the CDI interceptor to be active. In Open Liberty with CDI 4.0, it should work. But the bean is `@RequestScoped` which should be fine.\n\nLet me check if the issue is the entity manager transaction. The problem might be that `em.persist` followed by `em.flush()` is failing because the transaction isn't active. Let me enable more detailed logging:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1837,"cache_read_input_tokens":125562,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1837,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":310},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98f0c157-25c8-4522-ad5d-c073f4a9b639","uuid":"111fbc45-8572-4968-8dd3-a597bbb0721c"}
