{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01V4jjkhrDTUvE8HXp593pf2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"GET /roster/players returns `[]` (empty array, 200 OK). So the GET endpoints work. The issue is specifically with POST (transactional endpoints).\n\nThe problem is likely that `@Transactional` from `jakarta.transaction.Transactional` needs the CDI interceptor binding which is correctly set up, but the issue might be that the `RequestBean` is a JAX-RS resource AND a CDI bean simultaneously. In Quarkus, CDI interceptors work on all beans including JAX-RS resources. In Liberty (RESTEasy integration), the CDI interceptors might not fire on JAX-RS resources the same way.\n\nLet me verify by looking at the actual error. The `createLeague` wraps ALL exceptions as BAD_REQUEST, which is masking the real issue. The real issue might be `TransactionRequiredException` because the `@Transactional` interceptor isn't activating.\n\nLet me try modifying the approach: instead of relying on `@Transactional`, use `UserTransaction` explicitly or use the EJB approach with `@Stateless`:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":230,"cache_read_input_tokens":129352,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":230,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":384},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98f0c157-25c8-4522-ad5d-c073f4a9b639","uuid":"a59c5537-1419-4db4-9afd-4df7b0097f48"}
