{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014Hp4AneLMn6R5fVsCwYz12","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I can see the real error: `NullPointerException: Cannot invoke \"java.lang.String.toLowerCase()\" because the return value of \"quarkus.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails.getSport()\" is null`\n\nThe `LeagueDetails.getSport()` is returning null, which means the JSON body isn't being deserialized correctly. The JSON body `{\"id\":\"L1\",\"name\":\"Mountain\",\"sport\":\"Soccer\"}` should populate the `LeagueDetails` object. The issue is likely that `LeagueDetails` doesn't have proper getters/setters, or the JSON deserialization isn't working correctly with Liberty's default JSON-B provider.\n\nLet me check the `LeagueDetails` class:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1023,"cache_read_input_tokens":116126,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1023,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":286},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98f0c157-25c8-4522-ad5d-c073f4a9b639","uuid":"e8c1f115-6575-44ba-9035-0e2dc0fd5244"}
