{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01K9cU7taVwzrw6pggeakG8g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is clear - `LeagueDetails` has getters but NO setters. JSON-B (Jakarta JSON Binding) needs setters to deserialize JSON into objects. In Quarkus with Jackson (`resteasy-jackson`), the Jackson library can use field access or constructors. But in Open Liberty, the default JSON provider is JSON-B, which requires public setters for deserialization.\n\nI need to add setters to all three \"Details\" classes: `LeagueDetails`, `TeamDetails`, `PlayerDetails`."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1189,"cache_read_input_tokens":117149,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1189,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":333},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98f0c157-25c8-4522-ad5d-c073f4a9b639","uuid":"b41249a7-84ae-4dcd-a690-f1dab3cbc073"}
